The West African Examination Council (WAEC) has again extended registration for its 2020 West African Senior Secondary School Certificate Examination for private candidates.

According to a tweet on its Twitter handle, the new deadline is now Friday, November 13, 2020.

“WASSCE for private candidates, 2020 – second series: Further extension of registration period.

“Intending candidates should note that there has been a further extension of the registration period to Friday, November 13, 2020. Thank you,” the update read.

WAEC had initially extended the registration deadline to Friday, October 23, 2020.





